In addition to white noise, epidemic models are also subject to colored noise, namely telegraph noise, which switches the system from one environmental state to another14,15. Now we add telegraph noise in order to make our model be more realistic14,16. Telegraph noise can be interpreted as switching between two or more environmental states, which vary with factors such as humidity and temperature17,18. Switching between environment states is usually memory-free, and the waiting time for the next switch follows an exponential distribution19. Therefore, the state transition can be modeled using a continuous time markov chain (r(t))t≥0 that takes the values in the finite state space \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
